@jacob314: this looks to be the same issue as #2992?

I also had this issue now. 
@pq My bug report is the same of #2992 
This is my `flutter doctor -v`

Just for you to know, I removed the last four characters of my connected device, which it seems that is the identifier used to recognize my iPhone and so it is a private information. I don't think that this information could be useful to you and should be requested.

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!
